				<table width="100%" cellspacing="5">
				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">I am no 65c816 coder so I don't know much, but what is the argument against having 16-bit accumulator *and* index registers most of the time ? If this is a 16-bit CPU, normally most variables and registers should always be 16-bit, exept in rare cases where a smaller size is required, such as arrays with lots of data, which must be 8-bit, or communication with hardware registers. In those cases you could either do AND/OR trickery or shortly turn a register into a 8-bit time before returning to normal, depending on which one is more efficient.</div>

					<br clear="all" /><br />

						<table width="100%" cellspacing="0">
