						<div class="postbody">I do not pretend that my experience is in any way representative.  In fact I explicitly noted that I hadn't written much game logic yet.  If I'd had more comprehensive experience, my post would have been a lot shorter.<br /><br />But I think you may be exaggerating the rarity of the need for an 8-bit register.  It's encouraging to me that both byuu and Ramsis seem to handle this essentially the same way I do.<br /><br /><div class="quotetitle">Bregalad wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">The only reason to have 8-bit accumulator and 16-bit index is if you're not wanting to change that <em>ever</em></div><br />This makes no sense to me.</div>

